                                <graphEdge>
                                    <anchor>
                                    <position x="14.36698" y="13.65744"/>
                                    </anchor>
                                </graphEdge>
                            </anchorage>
                        </graphElement>
                    </graphicRepresentation>
                </designComments>
                <otherAnnotation type="html">
                    <text>
                        <div>
                            <p>
                                <b>
                                    <font face="times new roman,times" size="3">Parent class linking to and containing information about a primary care organisation or nominated pharmacy responsible for a patient over a period of time.</font>
                                </b>
                            </p>
                            <div>
                                <b>
                                    <font face="Times New Roman" size="3">
                                    <font face="Times New Roman" size="3">
                                    <font face="Times New Roman" size="3">
                                    <font
                                    face="Times New Roman" size="3">
                                    <font
                                    face="Times New Roman" size="3">
                                    <font
                                    face="Times New Roman" size="3">
                                    <font
                                    face="Times New Roman" size="3">If this item is being updated, then additionally, in order to control the update semantics, the following will also be present:</font>
                                    <ul>
                                    <li>

                                    <font
                                    face="Times New Roman" size="3">An <i>updateMode</i> attribute to indicate whether the item should be "added", "altered", or "removed" (mandatory)</font>
                                    </li>
                                    </ul>If this item is not being updated, and it is <i>CareProviderPaymentInfo</i> that is being updated, there will be no <i>updateMode</i> in this class, and the <i>code</i> attribute in this class will be set to '1'.                                                                               </font>
                                    </font>
                                    </font>
                                    </font>
                                    </font>
                                    </font>
                                </b>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </text>
                </otherAnnotation>
            </annotations>
            <attribute conformance="R" fixedValue="PCPR"
                isMandatory="true" isStructural="true"
                maximumMultiplicity="1" minimumMultiplicity="1"
                name="classCode" sortKey="1">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <p>
                                <font face="times new roman,times" size="3">Indicates that this is a Patient Care Provision act.</font>
                            </p>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="classCode"
                    className="Act" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="CS"/>
                <supplierDomainSpecification codingStrength="CNE" domainName="PCPR"/>
            </attribute>
            <attribute conformance="R" fixedValue="EVN"
                isMandatory="true" isStructural="true"
                maximumMultiplicity="1" minimumMultiplicity="1"
                name="moodCode" sortKey="2">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <p>
                                <font face="times new roman,times" size="3">Indicates that this is an Event.</font>
                            </p>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="moodCode"
                    className="Act" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="CS"/>
                <supplierDomainSpecification codingStrength="CNE" domainName="EVN"/>
            </attribute>
            <attribute isMandatory="false" maximumMultiplicity="1"
                minimumMultiplicity="0" name="id" sortKey="3">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <div>
                                <div>
                                    <font face="times new roman,times" size="3">A unique identifier for the patient care provision details. This identifier is allocated by the PDS.</font>
                                    <font face="Times New Roman" size="3">
                                    <font face="Times New Roman" size="3">
                                    <p>The Identifier External datatype flavour is used to carry this information as follows:</p>
                                    <ul>
                                    <li>The <i>root</i> attribute will contain an OID with the value "2.16.840.1.113883.2.1.3.2.4.18.1"</li>
                                    <li>The <i>extension</i> attribute will contain the PDS Allocated Object Identifier</li>
                                    </ul>
                                    <p>
                                    <font
                                    face="Times New Roman" size="3">This attribute shall be used in conjunction with the <i>updateMode</i> attribute of <i>PatientCareProvision </i>in the following way:</font>
                                    </p>
                                    <ul>
                                    <li>
                                    <font
                                    face="Times New Roman" size="3">This attribute shall be present when the <i>updateMode</i> is set to "altered" or "removed"</font>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>This attribute shall not be present when the <i>updateMode</i> is set to "added"</li>
                                    </ul>
                                    </font>
                                    </font>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="id" className="Act" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="II" typeSpecialisation="II.NPfIT.oid.mandatory"/>
            </attribute>
            <attribute isMandatory="false" maximumMultiplicity="1"
                minimumMultiplicity="0" name="code" sortKey="4">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <div>
                                <p>
                                    <font face="times new roman,times" size="3">Indicates the type of patient care provision.</font>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <font face="Times New Roman" size="3">The Coded with Code System datatype flavour is used to carry this information as follows:</font>
                                </p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                    <font face="Times New Roman" size="3">The <em>code</em> attribute will contain a value from the list of codes in the <u>PatientCareProvisionType</u> vocabulary</font>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                    <font face="Times New Roman" size="3">The <em>codeSystem</em> attribute will contain the OID "2.16.840.1.113883.2.1.3.2.4.17.37"</font>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                                <p>
                                    <font face="Times New Roman" size="3">NB Only one of each type of pharmacy data ("P1","P2" or "P3") can be provided.</font>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <font face="Times New Roman" size="3">
                                    <font face="Times New Roman" size="3">This attribute shall be used in conjunction with the <em>updateMode</em> attribute of <em>PatientCareProvision </em>in the following way:</font>
                                    <ul>
                                    <li>
                                    <font
                                    face="Times New Roman" size="3">This attribute shall not be present when the <em>updateMode</em> is set to "removed"</font>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>This attribute shall be present when the <em>updateMode</em> is set to "added" or "altered"</li>
                                    </ul>
                                    </font>
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="code" className="Act" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="CV"/>
                <supplierDomainSpecification codingStrength="CNE" domainName="PatientCareProvisionType"/>
            </attribute>
            <attribute isMandatory="false" maximumMultiplicity="1"
                minimumMultiplicity="0" name="effectiveTime" sortKey="10">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <p>The effective dates for the care provision relationship represented as a range, supplied in the <i>low </i>and <i>high </i>sub-elements. Both the <i>low </i>and <i>high </i>sub-elements are optional, allowing open-ended ranges to be specified. </p>
                            <p>The dates are full date without time.</p>
                            <p>May only be present where the PatientCareProvisionType is "1" (Primary care).</p>
                            <p>The effective from date (the <i>low </i>sub-element) must not be in the future.</p>
                            <p>
                                <font face="Times New Roman" size="3">
                                    <font face="Times New Roman" size="3">This attribute shall be used in conjunction with the <em>updateMode</em> attribute of <em>PatientCareProvision </em>in the following way:</font>
                                    <ul>
                                    <li>
                                    <font face="Times New Roman" size="3">This attribute shall not be present when the <em>updateMode</em> is set to "removed", except where NHAIS is removing a Primary Care registration, in which case, the effective to date (the <i>high</i> sub-element) may be present.</font>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                    <font face="Times New Roman" size="3">This attribute shall be present when the <i>updateMode</i> is set to "added" or "altered".</font>
                                    </li>
                                    </ul>
                                </font>
                            </p>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="effectiveTime"
                    className="Act" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="IVL">
                    <supplierBindingArgumentDatatype name="TS"/>
                </type>
            </attribute>
        </class>
    </ownedClass>
    <ownedClass>
