                                <b>The residential institution code in which the patient may live at the time that the care provider payment is administered.</b>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <b>This must be used in conjunction with the <i>updateMode</i> attribute of the <i>CareProviderPaymentInfo</i> class in the following way:</b>
                            </p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <b>This class must be present where the <i>updateMode  </i>is set to 'added' or 'altered'</b>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <b>This class must not be present where the <i>updateMode</i> is set to 'removed'.</b>
                                </li>

                            </ul>Note: Where the updateMode is set to "added" or "altered", at least one of the subject and pertinentInformation links and associated classes must be present (i.e. where Care Provider Payment data is being added or altered, at least one of Dispensing Authorisation Reason and Residential Institution code must be provided).<br type="_moz"/>
                        </div>
                    </text>
                </otherAnnotation>
